SUMMARY:2750 - Sourdough 101: Spring Edition
DESCRIPTION:Celebrate the freshness of early spring with Mike Wetherhold in this lively\, hands-on sourdough workshop. Known for his incredible loaves (and his equally famous dad jokes)\, Mike will guide you through the complete process of creating and maintaining your own sourdough starter\, mastering fermentation\, and baking loaves that are crisp on the outside and airy within. You will explore seasonal flavors and spring-inspired variations\, learn to care for your starter at home\, and leave confident to keep the baking going long after class ends. Expect plenty of Q&A time\, tasting\, and laughter along the way. \nDemonstration. BYOB. Ages 16 and up. Vegetarian. \n\nClassic Country Sourdough Loaf\nHerbed Spring Sourdough with Chives and Lemon Zest\nTasting of Fresh Sourdough with Freshly Made Butter and Seasonal Jams
URL:https://zestchef.com/class/2750-sourdough-101-spring-edition/
LOCATION:Zest Cooking School\, 1180 Erbs Quarry Road\, Lititz\, PA\, 17543\, United States
CATEGORIES:Basics and Techniques,Healthy Eating,Let's Bake,Masterclass,Vegetarian
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://zestchef.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/sourdough-101-scaled-e1743620961517.jpg
END:VEVENT
